{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Andorra – United States|Andorra|USA|filetype=svg}}

'''Andorra – United States relations''' are [[bilateral relations]] between [[Andorra]] and the [[United States]].

== History ==
[[File:Xavier Espot Miro with Obamas.jpg|thumb|right|Andorran Minister of External Affairs Xavier Espot Miro with President [[Barack Obama]]; 2009.]]
Andorra and the United States enjoy friendly relations. Diplomatic relations between both nations were established on 21 February 1995 after Andorra adopted a [[Constitution of Andorra|constitution]] establishing itself as a sovereign parliamentary democracy.<ref>[http://www.mae.ad/en/bilateral-and-consular-affairs/bilateral-affairs Andorran Ministry of Foreign Affairs: United States]</ref><ref name=Relations>[https://www.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/3164.htm State Department: U.S. Relations With Andorra]</ref> Since 2000, Andorra has participated in the U.S. [[Fulbright Program|Fulbright Exchange Program]] and works together with the United States on sharing of confiscated proceeds and instrumentalities of crimes.<ref name=Relations />

There are no significant trade or investments between the two nations. Andorra participates in the American [[Visa Waiver Program]]. The United States ambassador to [[Spain]] is accredited to Andorra, however, the American consul-general in [[Barcelona]] carries out the day-to-day relations with Andorra. Andorra is accredited to the United States from its Permanent Mission to the United Nations based in [[New York City]].<ref name=Relations />

