[[File:Biete Amanuel.jpg|thumb|The rock church Biete Amanuel in Lalibela, Ethiopia]]
'''Biete Amanuel''' is an underground [[Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church|Orthodox]] monolith rock-cut church located in [[Lalibela]], [[Ethiopia]]. The edifice was built during the [[Kingdom of Axum]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lonelyplanet.com/ethiopia/northern-ethiopia/lalibela/sights/religious/bet-amanuel|title=Biete Amanuel|author=Lonely Planet Guide}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/lali/hd_lali.htm|title=The Rock-hewn Churches of Lalibela|author=The Metropolitan Museum of Art}}</ref> It is part of UNESCO World Heritage Site at Lalibela.<ref name="unesco">{{cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/18|title=Rock-Hewn Churches, Lalibela|author=UNESCO World Heritage Centre|work=unesco.org}}</ref> Biete Amanuel (House of Emmanuel) is possibly the former royal chapel.<ref>[[Lalibela]]</ref>

