[[File:Cannabis College.png|thumb|Cannabis College entrance.]] The '''Cannabis College''' is a [[non-profit]] information centre located in the centre of [[Amsterdam]]'s historic [[Red-light district|Red Light District]] in [[The Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.timeout.com/amsterdam/en/attractions-and-museums/cannabis-college | title=Cannabis College | publisher=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]] | accessdate=20 July 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Attraction_Review-g188590-d4045988-Reviews-Cannabis_College-Amsterdam_North_Holland_Province.html | title=Cannabis College | publisher=[[TripAdvisor]] | accessdate=20 July 2014 }}</ref> Opened in 1998, the info centre features displays of the many and varied uses for [[Cannabis sativa]] and industrial [[hemp]], as well as the history of human interaction with the plant. Everything from hemp building materials and plastics to [[medical Cannabis]] and worldwide legislation is covered.
The basement of the building hosts an organic flowering Cannabis garden, cultivated by an expert grower and utilizing some of the most reliable strains and popular organic nutrients.
There is also a Cannabis College in [[Garberville, California]].<ref name="Vishva Samani">{{cite news | last= Samani | first= Vishva | url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/9480322.stm | title= Blurred lines in California's cannabis capital | publisher= [[BBC News]] | date= 9 May 2011 | accessdate= }}</ref>
