'''''L'Espérance''''' ('The Hope') was a newspaper published in [[Guinea]], appearing in the period shortly after the relaxation of Guinean press laws in 1993. The newspaper was published by the Guinean [[Red Cross]]. By 1995 publication of the newspaper was discontinued.<ref>Camara, Mohamed Saliou. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=coRC9igyNdgC&pg=PA199 His Master's Voice: Mass Communication and Single-Party Politics in Guinea Under Sékou Touré]''. Trenton, NJ [u.a.]: Africa World Press, 2005. p. 199</ref>
