The '''Lithuanian Institute of History''' ({{lang-lt|Lietuvos istorijos institutas}}) is a state-funded research institution in [[Lithuania]]. Governed by national law,<ref>{{cite web|title=Lietuvos Istorijos Instituto Istatai|publisher=[[Seimas]] (Parliament) of the [[Republic of Lithuania]]|url=http://www.lrs.lt/pls/proj/dokpaieska.dok_priedas?p_id=44314|accessdate=2010-03-03|language=lt}}</ref> it is the country's main institution of history research, concentrating mostly on the [[history of Lithuania]] and its neighbouring states.

The institute employs 126 people; 64 of them have Ph.D. degrees and 4 are hablitated doctors. Its director is [[Rimantas Miknys]]. The institute is divided into 7 sections (archaeology, cities, ethnology, archaeography, [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]], 19th century and 20th century). It also has its own library, collection of manuscripts, and publishing house. It was established in 1941 as a division of the [[Lithuanian Academy of Sciences]].

As of 2007, the institute was working on 15 projects,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.istorija.lt/html/index.html |title=Projects list at Lithuanian Institute of History webpage|accessdate=2007-01-13|language=lt}}</ref> main of them is 12-volume [[History of Lithuania (book)|academic history of Lithuania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.istorija.lt/html/ldk1.html |title=Project summary at Lithuanian Institute of History webpage |accessdate=2007-01-13 |language=lt |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070113180115/http://www.istorija.lt/html/ldk1.html |archivedate=2007-01-13 |df= }}</ref> The institute publishes semi-annual journal ''Lietuvos istorijos metraštis''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.istorija.lt/lim/index.html|title=List of latest issues|accessdate=2007-01-13|language=lt|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070118004537/http://www.istorija.lt/lim/index.html|archivedate=2007-01-18|df=}}</ref> and annual English journal ''Lithuanian Historical Studies''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.istorija.lt/lhs/index.html |title=List of latest issues|accessdate=2007-01-13}}</ref>

