{{Infobox Union |name= NTL |country= [[Norway]] |affiliation= [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions|LO]] |members= 50 000 |full_name= Norwegian Civil Service Union |native_name= Norsk Tjenestemannslag |image= [[File:Norsk Tjenestemannslag logo.png|125px]] |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Oslo]], Norway |people= [[John Leirvaag]], president |website= [http://www.ntl.no www.ntl.no] |footnotes= }} [[File:Ntl foto brage aronsen.jpg|thumb|Members of the Norwegian trade union Norsk Tjenestemannslag (The Norwegian Civil Service Union) during a strike in 2012.]] The '''Norwegian Civil Service Union''' (NTL) is a [[trade union]] in [[Norway]]. It has a membership of nearly 50,000 and is affiliated with the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]] (LO). '''The Norwegian Civil Service Union''' was founded in 1947.
